{"cues": [{"duration": 5.12, "start": 0.0, "text": "In late September 2025, Deepseek"}, {"duration": 4.319, "start": 2.96, "text": "released an experimental model. This"}, {"duration": 4.16, "start": 5.12, "text": "latest model introduced a new attention"}, {"duration": 6.161, "start": 7.279, "text": "barren known as Deepseek sparse"}, {"duration": 6.399, "start": 9.28, "text": "attention or DSA. By leveraging DSA, the"}, {"duration": 4.96, "start": 13.44, "text": "model matches the performance of earlier"}, {"duration": 6.641, "start": 15.679, "text": "versions but drastically reduce compute"}, {"duration": 6.24, "start": 18.4, "text": "costs cutting API pricing by 50%. But"}, {"duration": 4.799, "start": 22.32, "text": "how can we make attention mechanism so"}, {"duration": 5.12, "start": 24.64, "text": "efficient? As usual, let's build out the"}, {"duration": 4.4, "start": 27.119, "text": "method from the first principle. But if"}, {"duration": 4.08, "start": 29.76, "text": "you are already familiar with some of"}, {"duration": 4.401, "start": 31.519, "text": "the basics, feel free to jump ahead to"}, {"duration": 4.08, "start": 33.84, "text": "the relevant chapters."}, {"duration": 3.76, "start": 35.92, "text": "At a high level, when given the input"}, {"duration": 4.799, "start": 37.92, "text": "prompt, the large language model"}, {"duration": 6.399, "start": 39.68, "text": "generates an output response. But how"}, {"duration": 5.201, "start": 42.719, "text": "does a model make sense of language? The"}, {"duration": 4.881, "start": 46.079, "text": "very first step is to break up the text"}, {"duration": 5.92, "start": 47.92, "text": "into pieces we call tokens."}, {"duration": 4.64, "start": 50.96, "text": "Each token is assigned to a unique ID in"}, {"duration": 4.08, "start": 53.84, "text": "a dictionary."}, {"duration": 4.72, "start": 55.6, "text": "This is known as tokenization."}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 57.92, "text": "But the token ID alone does not capture"}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 60.32, "text": "the semantic meanings of the words."}, {"duration": 4.4, "start": 63.28, "text": "Therefore, we map individual tokens into"}, {"duration": 3.52, "start": 65.68, "text": "d-dimensional vectors called token"}, {"duration": 3.92, "start": 67.68, "text": "embeddings."}, {"duration": 4.56, "start": 69.2, "text": "In this D- dimensional space, words with"}, {"duration": 4.96, "start": 71.6, "text": "similar meanings have embeddings that"}, {"duration": 5.359, "start": 73.76, "text": "are close to each other. However, these"}, {"duration": 5.44, "start": 76.56, "text": "token embeddings on their own lock any"}, {"duration": 5.281, "start": 79.119, "text": "information about the context."}, {"duration": 5.119, "start": 82.0, "text": "This is where attention comes in."}, {"duration": 5.2, "start": 84.4, "text": "Attention allows the model to determine"}, {"duration": 4.401, "start": 87.119, "text": "how each token contributes to gather"}, {"duration": 4.879, "start": 89.6, "text": "contextual information from the input"}, {"duration": 5.76, "start": 91.52, "text": "sequence. We measure the relationship"}, {"duration": 6.481, "start": 94.479, "text": "between tokens in a learn space"}, {"duration": 7.6, "start": 97.28, "text": "specified by query and key matrices. The"}, {"duration": 7.439, "start": 100.96, "text": "query matrix have shape D * DK where D"}, {"duration": 7.76, "start": 104.88, "text": "is the embedding size about 7,000 in DC"}, {"duration": 6.161, "start": 108.399, "text": "V3 or DC R1 and DK is the dimension of"}, {"duration": 4.159, "start": 112.64, "text": "the query vector."}, {"duration": 4.64, "start": 114.56, "text": "We can first compute the query vectors"}, {"duration": 5.28, "start": 116.799, "text": "by multiplying each token embedding with"}, {"duration": 6.4, "start": 119.2, "text": "the query matrix WQ."}, {"duration": 8.561, "start": 122.079, "text": "Multiplying a 1x d embedding vector with"}, {"duration": 6.56, "start": 125.6, "text": "a d by dk matrix result in a 1x dk query"}, {"duration": 3.92, "start": 130.64, "text": "vector."}, {"duration": 4.56, "start": 132.16, "text": "Similarly, we compute a key vector by"}, {"duration": 4.96, "start": 134.56, "text": "multiplying each token embedding with"}, {"duration": 5.2, "start": 136.72, "text": "the key matrix wk."}, {"duration": 5.28, "start": 139.52, "text": "We quantify the relevance from one token"}, {"duration": 5.28, "start": 141.92, "text": "to another using the vector dotproduct"}, {"duration": 4.079, "start": 144.8, "text": "between the extracted query and key"}, {"duration": 4.399, "start": 147.2, "text": "vectors."}, {"duration": 6.161, "start": 148.879, "text": "Here the dotproduct refracts how similar"}, {"duration": 6.081, "start": 151.599, "text": "the query and key vectors are. As the"}, {"duration": 5.52, "start": 155.04, "text": "model generates its response one token"}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 157.68, "text": "at a time. In other words, in an auto"}, {"duration": 4.959, "start": 160.56, "text": "reggressive manner, we consider only the"}, {"duration": 5.52, "start": 163.04, "text": "relevance between each token and all"}, {"duration": 5.041, "start": 165.519, "text": "tokens that came before it. Since the"}, {"duration": 4.8, "start": 168.56, "text": "dot product between the query and key"}, {"duration": 5.6, "start": 170.56, "text": "vectors can yield both positive and"}, {"duration": 5.76, "start": 173.36, "text": "negative values, we apply a softmax"}, {"duration": 5.68, "start": 176.16, "text": "function to convert this row scores into"}, {"duration": 5.199, "start": 179.12, "text": "normalized probability distributions."}, {"duration": 5.759, "start": 181.84, "text": "These resulting values are known as the"}, {"duration": 5.601, "start": 184.319, "text": "attention scores. The attention scores"}, {"duration": 4.801, "start": 187.599, "text": "indicate how much inference each token"}, {"duration": 5.679, "start": 189.92, "text": "should have when updating the embedding"}, {"duration": 4.96, "start": 192.4, "text": "of a particular token. For each token,"}, {"duration": 5.601, "start": 195.599, "text": "we compute the corresponding value"}, {"duration": 6.32, "start": 197.36, "text": "vector using a value matrix WV."}, {"duration": 4.319, "start": 201.2, "text": "This extracts the contextual information"}, {"duration": 4.72, "start": 203.68, "text": "that could be transferred to other"}, {"duration": 5.521, "start": 205.519, "text": "tokens. We then aggregate these value"}, {"duration": 5.6, "start": 208.4, "text": "vectors into a single representation for"}, {"duration": 4.72, "start": 211.04, "text": "each token by computing a weighted sum"}, {"duration": 3.92, "start": 214.0, "text": "where the weights are given by the"}, {"duration": 4.559, "start": 215.76, "text": "attention scores."}, {"duration": 4.48, "start": 217.92, "text": "But here the dimensionality of the value"}, {"duration": 5.28, "start": 220.319, "text": "vectors are much smaller than the"}, {"duration": 5.6, "start": 222.4, "text": "embedding dimension D. Therefore we use"}, {"duration": 4.72, "start": 225.599, "text": "an output matrix to convert the output"}, {"duration": 4.56, "start": 228.0, "text": "vectors back to the same dimensionality"}, {"duration": 4.721, "start": 230.319, "text": "of token embeddings."}, {"duration": 5.28, "start": 232.56, "text": "We then add these residual embeddings to"}, {"duration": 5.199, "start": 235.04, "text": "update the original token embeddings."}, {"duration": 4.479, "start": 237.84, "text": "This self attention mechanism enables"}, {"duration": 5.28, "start": 240.239, "text": "the model to incorporate contextual"}, {"duration": 5.441, "start": 242.319, "text": "information into each embedding ensuring"}, {"duration": 4.161, "start": 245.519, "text": "that the refined embeddings capture"}, {"duration": 4.96, "start": 247.76, "text": "relevant details from the entire"}, {"duration": 5.52, "start": 249.68, "text": "sequence. Here the trainable parameters"}, {"duration": 4.32, "start": 252.72, "text": "of a self attention layer include these"}, {"duration": 3.92, "start": 255.2, "text": "four matrixes."}, {"duration": 4.56, "start": 257.04, "text": "Here we only illustrate the computation"}, {"duration": 4.639, "start": 259.12, "text": "for the first attention layer but all"}, {"duration": 5.039, "start": 261.6, "text": "subsequent attention layers in a deep"}, {"duration": 5.041, "start": 263.759, "text": "model operate in the same way."}, {"duration": 5.28, "start": 266.639, "text": "However, explicitly writing out each"}, {"duration": 4.8, "start": 268.8, "text": "vector can quickly go out of hand."}, {"duration": 5.28, "start": 271.919, "text": "Luckily, we can represent [music] the"}, {"duration": 6.64, "start": 273.6, "text": "computation in a simple compact form. We"}, {"duration": 6.72, "start": 277.199, "text": "denote the stack of query vectors as Q"}, {"duration": 6.08, "start": 280.24, "text": "and a stack of key vectors as K. This"}, {"duration": 5.041, "start": 283.919, "text": "allows us to concisely express all the"}, {"duration": 5.52, "start": 286.32, "text": "dotproducts between pairs of vectors"}, {"duration": 6.64, "start": 288.96, "text": "using the matrix multiplication Q"}, {"duration": 5.919, "start": 291.84, "text": "transpose. We add a masking matrix M to"}, {"duration": 5.84, "start": 295.6, "text": "ensure that the tokens only attend to"}, {"duration": 5.841, "start": 297.759, "text": "tokens that come before it and itself."}, {"duration": 5.92, "start": 301.44, "text": "With the attention weights, we express"}, {"duration": 5.76, "start": 303.6, "text": "the output matrix O in matrix form. More"}, {"duration": 6.72, "start": 307.36, "text": "concisely, we denote the attention"}, {"duration": 6.88, "start": 309.36, "text": "mechanism as a function of Q, K, and B."}, {"duration": 4.8, "start": 314.08, "text": "The residual embeddings are just the"}, {"duration": 5.6, "start": 316.24, "text": "matrix multiplication of the matrix O"}, {"duration": 5.759, "start": 318.88, "text": "and the output matrix W."}, {"duration": 5.359, "start": 321.84, "text": "Let's put it together visually. We"}, {"duration": 4.801, "start": 324.639, "text": "extract the query key [music] and value"}, {"duration": 4.801, "start": 327.199, "text": "vectors from the token embeddings using"}, {"duration": 4.479, "start": 329.44, "text": "the corresponding matrices. We then"}, {"duration": 4.08, "start": 332.0, "text": "compute the output O with attention"}, {"duration": 4.72, "start": 333.919, "text": "mechanism and produce the residual"}, {"duration": 4.8, "start": 336.08, "text": "embeddings delta X using the output"}, {"duration": 5.201, "start": 338.639, "text": "matrix WO."}, {"duration": 6.159, "start": 340.88, "text": "But here is a problem. Using a single"}, {"duration": 5.44, "start": 343.84, "text": "query key and value matrix is not enough"}, {"duration": 4.16, "start": 347.039, "text": "to capture the complex relationships"}, {"duration": 4.32, "start": 349.28, "text": "between tokens. [music]"}, {"duration": 6.081, "start": 351.199, "text": "To address this, we introduce multiple"}, {"duration": 5.92, "start": 353.6, "text": "sets of query key and value matrices,"}, {"duration": 4.8, "start": 357.28, "text": "enabling the model to learn and"}, {"duration": 5.44, "start": 359.52, "text": "represent diverse types of relationships"}, {"duration": 5.52, "start": 362.08, "text": "between tokens. This is achieved by"}, {"duration": 6.32, "start": 364.96, "text": "extending the size of query key and"}, {"duration": 6.4, "start": 367.6, "text": "value matrixes. Here h is the number of"}, {"duration": 5.199, "start": 371.28, "text": "heads. We show four hats in the"}, {"duration": 6.24, "start": 374.0, "text": "illustration but in practice the number"}, {"duration": 8.961, "start": 376.479, "text": "of hats can be much larger like 128 in"}, {"duration": 7.6, "start": 380.24, "text": "DC V3 MDC R1. We split the query key and"}, {"duration": 4.72, "start": 385.44, "text": "value matrices into edge group [music]"}, {"duration": 4.079, "start": 387.84, "text": "and compute the attention for each group"}, {"duration": 4.159, "start": 390.16, "text": "separately."}, {"duration": 6.4, "start": 391.919, "text": "This gives us a collection of attention"}, {"duration": 6.081, "start": 394.319, "text": "outputs 01 O2 to O."}, {"duration": 5.121, "start": 398.319, "text": "We concatenate the outputs of multiple"}, {"duration": 5.919, "start": 400.4, "text": "hands together and use our output matrix"}, {"duration": 6.56, "start": 403.44, "text": "WO to produce the residual embedding"}, {"duration": 6.801, "start": 406.319, "text": "delta X. This is known as multihat"}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 410.0, "text": "attention, a core building block of the"}, {"duration": 6.16, "start": 413.12, "text": "transformer architecture that's behind"}, {"duration": 6.16, "start": 415.36, "text": "the success of LLM today. Thanks for"}, {"duration": 5.52, "start": 419.28, "text": "masking, the model can compute attention"}, {"duration": 6.48, "start": 421.52, "text": "for all the tokens at the same time."}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 424.8, "text": "This is called the preilling stage."}, {"duration": 5.12, "start": 428.0, "text": "Things become interesting when we start"}, {"duration": 5.84, "start": 430.16, "text": "generating the output response. Let's"}, {"duration": 5.76, "start": 433.12, "text": "say X7 is the first token in the output"}, {"duration": 6.0, "start": 436.0, "text": "response. Our goal now is to compute the"}, {"duration": 6.0, "start": 438.88, "text": "attention output 07 using the context"}, {"duration": 5.28, "start": 442.0, "text": "provided by the preceding tokens."}, {"duration": 5.12, "start": 444.88, "text": "Similar to the prevailing stage, we"}, {"duration": 4.96, "start": 447.28, "text": "extract the query key vectors using the"}, {"duration": 4.319, "start": 450.0, "text": "corresponding matrixes."}, {"duration": 4.239, "start": 452.24, "text": "With these vectors, we compute the"}, {"duration": 4.88, "start": 454.319, "text": "attention scores by taking the dot"}, {"duration": 4.56, "start": 456.479, "text": "product and normalizing them with a soft"}, {"duration": 4.161, "start": 459.199, "text": "max function."}, {"duration": 5.6, "start": 461.039, "text": "We can then produce the attention output"}, {"duration": 5.279, "start": 463.36, "text": "07 by computing the weighted sum of the"}, {"duration": 4.481, "start": 466.639, "text": "value vectors."}, {"duration": 5.201, "start": 468.639, "text": "During this process, the key and value"}, {"duration": 6.16, "start": 471.12, "text": "vectors from the previous tokens do not"}, {"duration": 5.6, "start": 473.84, "text": "change at all. This is true across"}, {"duration": 4.96, "start": 477.28, "text": "multiple attention hands in all"}, {"duration": 5.68, "start": 479.44, "text": "attention layers. Recomputing these"}, {"duration": 4.399, "start": 482.24, "text": "vectors every time for each new token is"}, {"duration": 3.759, "start": 485.12, "text": "wasteful."}, {"duration": 4.481, "start": 486.639, "text": "A simple solution is to store the key"}, {"duration": 6.16, "start": 488.879, "text": "and value vectors from previous tokens"}, {"duration": 6.56, "start": 491.12, "text": "in memory and reuse them when needed."}, {"duration": 6.72, "start": 495.039, "text": "This is a technique known as key value"}, {"duration": 6.32, "start": 497.68, "text": "caching or KV caching for short. The KB"}, {"duration": 4.801, "start": 501.759, "text": "caching helps avoid unnecessary"}, {"duration": 4.72, "start": 504.0, "text": "computation and therefore speed up the"}, {"duration": 4.4, "start": 506.56, "text": "decoding process."}, {"duration": 4.799, "start": 508.72, "text": "How about query vectors?"}, {"duration": 4.959, "start": 510.96, "text": "As we can see, all these entries are"}, {"duration": 5.681, "start": 513.519, "text": "masked out and have no effect on the"}, {"duration": 5.521, "start": 515.919, "text": "attention output. This is why we do not"}, {"duration": 6.4, "start": 519.2, "text": "need to cache any of the previous query"}, {"duration": 7.28, "start": 521.44, "text": "vectors. KB caching is very effective,"}, {"duration": 6.16, "start": 525.6, "text": "but it's memory intensive. Let's take"}, {"duration": 6.32, "start": 528.72, "text": "the model architecture of deepse V3 or"}, {"duration": 6.72, "start": 531.76, "text": "R1 as reference. The total memory"}, {"duration": 6.799, "start": 535.04, "text": "required for the KB caching is 2 * KB"}, {"duration": 6.24, "start": 538.48, "text": "dimension time position time number of"}, {"duration": 6.161, "start": 541.839, "text": "heads time number of layers times"}, {"duration": 6.799, "start": 544.72, "text": "sequence length two because we need to"}, {"duration": 6.959, "start": 548.0, "text": "cache both the key and value vectors."}, {"duration": 6.481, "start": 551.519, "text": "For each vector we need to store 128"}, {"duration": 7.361, "start": 554.959, "text": "numbers. For each number we need two"}, {"duration": 8.0, "start": 558.0, "text": "bytes for float 16 precision and we have"}, {"duration": 5.84, "start": 562.32, "text": "128 attention hands in a layer and 61"}, {"duration": 4.959, "start": 566.0, "text": "layers in total."}, {"duration": 6.08, "start": 568.16, "text": "Suppose we have a sequence of 32k"}, {"duration": 8.32, "start": 570.959, "text": "tokens. The total memory required for"}, {"duration": 7.92, "start": 574.24, "text": "the KB cache amounts to 131 GB."}, {"duration": 4.56, "start": 579.279, "text": "This is a lot of memory."}, {"duration": 3.28, "start": 582.16, "text": "How can we reduce the memory"}, {"duration": 3.68, "start": 583.839, "text": "requirements?"}, {"duration": 5.2, "start": 585.44, "text": "Let's revisit the multi-head attention"}, {"duration": 5.841, "start": 587.519, "text": "mechanism. We cannot adjust the KB"}, {"duration": 5.44, "start": 590.64, "text": "dimension, the position or the number of"}, {"duration": 4.72, "start": 593.36, "text": "layers. But maybe we can look at the"}, {"duration": 4.4, "start": 596.08, "text": "number of hands."}, {"duration": 5.759, "start": 598.08, "text": "One simple idea is to reduce the number"}, {"duration": 6.799, "start": 600.48, "text": "of hands for key and value matrices from"}, {"duration": 6.56, "start": 603.839, "text": "H to one. This means that we produce"}, {"duration": 6.721, "start": 607.279, "text": "only one copy of key and value vectors"}, {"duration": 6.56, "start": 610.399, "text": "for each token in a layer. The key and"}, {"duration": 5.12, "start": 614.0, "text": "value vectors are then shared across all"}, {"duration": 5.12, "start": 616.959, "text": "attention hats."}, {"duration": 6.64, "start": 619.12, "text": "This is known as multi-query attention"}, {"duration": 6.481, "start": 622.079, "text": "or MQA for short. Let's now compare the"}, {"duration": 5.519, "start": 625.76, "text": "memory requirements of MQA with the"}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 628.56, "text": "original multi-headand attention."}, {"duration": 6.641, "start": 631.279, "text": "Multiand attention requires 4 mgabytes"}, {"duration": 7.44, "start": 633.92, "text": "of memory per token. In contrast, MQA"}, {"duration": 6.72, "start": 637.92, "text": "requires only 31 kilobytes per token."}, {"duration": 4.8, "start": 641.36, "text": "It's a 128fold reduction in memory"}, {"duration": 4.56, "start": 644.64, "text": "usage."}, {"duration": 5.52, "start": 646.16, "text": "However, there's a catch. Multi-query"}, {"duration": 4.8, "start": 649.2, "text": "attention sacrifice the ability to"}, {"duration": 5.92, "start": 651.68, "text": "capture complex relationships between"}, {"duration": 6.16, "start": 654.0, "text": "tokens. As a result, MQA's performance"}, {"duration": 5.52, "start": 657.6, "text": "degrades considerably compared to the"}, {"duration": 5.2, "start": 660.16, "text": "original multi-and attention."}, {"duration": 4.56, "start": 663.12, "text": "Perhaps the reason is that we go too far"}, {"duration": 5.599, "start": 665.36, "text": "in reducing the number of hands all the"}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 667.68, "text": "way from 128 to one."}, {"duration": 5.201, "start": 670.959, "text": "Alternatively, we can reduce the number"}, {"duration": 7.6, "start": 673.04, "text": "of heads just to a smaller value denoted"}, {"duration": 6.64, "start": 676.16, "text": "as ng where G indicates groups. For"}, {"duration": 5.28, "start": 680.64, "text": "example, here we set the number of"}, {"duration": 5.12, "start": 682.8, "text": "groups as two. This means that we"}, {"duration": 7.76, "start": 685.92, "text": "produce two distinct key and value"}, {"duration": 8.24, "start": 687.92, "text": "vectors for each token K1 K2 and V1 B2."}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 693.68, "text": "The key and value vectors are then"}, {"duration": 4.239, "start": 696.16, "text": "shared across attention has within each"}, {"duration": 4.0, "start": 699.04, "text": "group."}, {"duration": 6.801, "start": 700.399, "text": "This is known as group query attention"}, {"duration": 6.0, "start": 703.04, "text": "or GQA for short. GQA strikes a balance"}, {"duration": 4.4, "start": 707.2, "text": "between the memory efficiency of"}, {"duration": 5.76, "start": 709.04, "text": "multi-query attention and the expressive"}, {"duration": 6.0, "start": 711.6, "text": "power of multiand attention. It's a"}, {"duration": 6.08, "start": 714.8, "text": "popular choice in modern ams including"}, {"duration": 6.4, "start": 717.6, "text": "llama from Madam Quinn from Alibaba and"}, {"duration": 6.24, "start": 720.88, "text": "Gamma from Google. For instance, if we"}, {"duration": 5.76, "start": 724.0, "text": "divide 128 attention hands into 16"}, {"duration": 5.279, "start": 727.12, "text": "groups, we achieve an A-fold reduction"}, {"duration": 4.879, "start": 729.76, "text": "in memory usage compared to standard"}, {"duration": 4.081, "start": 732.399, "text": "multi-headand attention."}, {"duration": 4.801, "start": 734.639, "text": "Let's try understanding group query"}, {"duration": 5.52, "start": 736.48, "text": "attention from another perspective. Here"}, {"duration": 5.04, "start": 739.44, "text": "we use the key and value matrices to"}, {"duration": 5.68, "start": 742.0, "text": "compute the two sets of key and value"}, {"duration": 5.2, "start": 744.48, "text": "vectors. We can duplicate these vectors"}, {"duration": 5.52, "start": 747.68, "text": "so we can use them for multi-headand"}, {"duration": 5.68, "start": 749.68, "text": "attention. This process of duplication"}, {"duration": 5.759, "start": 753.2, "text": "can be written as a simple matrix"}, {"duration": 7.36, "start": 755.36, "text": "multiplication where I DK is an identity"}, {"duration": 6.481, "start": 758.959, "text": "matrix of size DK by DK."}, {"duration": 6.96, "start": 762.72, "text": "Let's give this matrix a name as the up"}, {"duration": 6.88, "start": 765.44, "text": "projection matrix W K up. Similarly, the"}, {"duration": 4.56, "start": 769.68, "text": "process of duplicating the value vectors"}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 772.32, "text": "can be expressed as a matrix"}, {"duration": 7.68, "start": 774.24, "text": "multiplication where IDB is identity"}, {"duration": 7.36, "start": 777.68, "text": "matrix of size DV by DV. We call this"}, {"duration": 4.64, "start": 781.92, "text": "matrix as the up projection matrix WV"}, {"duration": 3.919, "start": 785.04, "text": "up."}, {"duration": 5.2, "start": 786.56, "text": "Now we can further simplify the key and"}, {"duration": 5.281, "start": 788.959, "text": "value matrices by concatenating them"}, {"duration": 7.04, "start": 791.76, "text": "along the column dimensions"}, {"duration": 8.159, "start": 794.24, "text": "and give it a new name as W KB down."}, {"duration": 6.24, "start": 798.8, "text": "This expression reveals that in GQA the"}, {"duration": 5.281, "start": 802.399, "text": "key vectors are obtained through a low"}, {"duration": 5.76, "start": 805.04, "text": "rank factorization of the original key"}, {"duration": 4.88, "start": 807.68, "text": "matrix. Same things apply to the value"}, {"duration": 4.96, "start": 810.8, "text": "vectors."}, {"duration": 5.2, "start": 812.56, "text": "But the lowren factorization in GQA is"}, {"duration": 4.8, "start": 815.76, "text": "somewhat restricted."}, {"duration": 6.0, "start": 817.76, "text": "For example, it groups the key and value"}, {"duration": 6.16, "start": 820.56, "text": "vectors separately and use a fixed"}, {"duration": 5.6, "start": 823.76, "text": "simple up projection matrix. We can"}, {"duration": 4.64, "start": 826.72, "text": "extend this further by training both the"}, {"duration": 3.52, "start": 829.36, "text": "down projection and up projection"}, {"duration": 4.64, "start": 831.36, "text": "matrices."}, {"duration": 5.6, "start": 832.88, "text": "The down projection matrix WKB down"}, {"duration": 6.24, "start": 836.0, "text": "compresses the token embeddings into a"}, {"duration": 7.919, "start": 838.48, "text": "lowdimensional feature vector CB."}, {"duration": 6.959, "start": 842.24, "text": "The up projection matrix WK up and WV up"}, {"duration": 6.081, "start": 846.399, "text": "then map this compressed vector back to"}, {"duration": 5.681, "start": 849.199, "text": "the key and value vectors. The learn"}, {"duration": 5.12, "start": 852.48, "text": "projection matrix allows the model to"}, {"duration": 6.079, "start": 854.88, "text": "produce distinct key and value vectors"}, {"duration": 5.84, "start": 857.6, "text": "for each attention head. This is the"}, {"duration": 5.281, "start": 860.959, "text": "core idea behind multi-headand latent"}, {"duration": 5.759, "start": 863.44, "text": "attention. The dimensionality of the"}, {"duration": 4.719, "start": 866.24, "text": "compressed vector DC is much smaller"}, {"duration": 5.76, "start": 869.199, "text": "compared to the full multi-headand"}, {"duration": 6.56, "start": 870.959, "text": "attention. For instance, in deepc V3 R1,"}, {"duration": 4.801, "start": 874.959, "text": "the compressed dimension DC is set to"}, {"duration": 4.481, "start": 877.519, "text": "576."}, {"duration": 4.319, "start": 879.76, "text": "In standard multi-head attention, we"}, {"duration": 4.24, "start": 882.0, "text": "will need the number of heads times the"}, {"duration": 5.041, "start": 884.079, "text": "dimension of the key and value vectors"}, {"duration": 6.0, "start": 886.24, "text": "for each head times two for key and"}, {"duration": 6.32, "start": 889.12, "text": "value vectors. As a result, this amounts"}, {"duration": 6.159, "start": 892.24, "text": "to 57 times reduction in memory usage"}, {"duration": 6.32, "start": 895.44, "text": "compared to multi-head attention. Not"}, {"duration": 5.841, "start": 898.399, "text": "only does MLA reduce memory usage, it"}, {"duration": 4.56, "start": 901.76, "text": "also slightly improves the performance"}, {"duration": 4.8, "start": 904.24, "text": "compared to models using multihat"}, {"duration": 5.199, "start": 906.32, "text": "attention. In addition to the key and"}, {"duration": 5.2, "start": 909.04, "text": "value matrices, we can also apply low"}, {"duration": 5.601, "start": 911.519, "text": "rank compression to the query matrix."}, {"duration": 5.68, "start": 914.24, "text": "Here the upper ejection matrix WQ takes"}, {"duration": 5.68, "start": 917.12, "text": "the compressed vector of dimension DC"}, {"duration": 5.039, "start": 919.92, "text": "and reconstruct the query vectors. This"}, {"duration": 6.56, "start": 922.8, "text": "result in query vectors more multiple"}, {"duration": 7.44, "start": 924.959, "text": "heads with size DK * H. While this does"}, {"duration": 5.52, "start": 929.36, "text": "not decrease KB cache memory usage, it"}, {"duration": 4.56, "start": 932.399, "text": "can still help reduce activation memory"}, {"duration": 4.399, "start": 934.88, "text": "during training."}, {"duration": 4.081, "start": 936.959, "text": "Now at the first glance it may seem that"}, {"duration": 4.56, "start": 939.279, "text": "we will need an extra matrix"}, {"duration": 6.0, "start": 941.04, "text": "multiplication as the tradeoff for KV"}, {"duration": 5.761, "start": 943.839, "text": "cache memory reduction but we can"}, {"duration": 5.84, "start": 947.04, "text": "actually apply a neat trick to avoid"}, {"duration": 6.239, "start": 949.6, "text": "this extra computation during inference."}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 952.88, "text": "Here's how it works. Recall that the"}, {"duration": 5.201, "start": 955.839, "text": "residual embedding delta X is the"}, {"duration": 6.399, "start": 958.24, "text": "multiplication of the attention output O"}, {"duration": 5.76, "start": 961.04, "text": "and the output matrix WO. The output O"}, {"duration": 4.481, "start": 964.639, "text": "is the concatenation of the attention"}, {"duration": 5.52, "start": 966.8, "text": "outputs from each individual attention"}, {"duration": 6.48, "start": 969.12, "text": "hand. Let's write this out explicitly"}, {"duration": 6.4, "start": 972.32, "text": "using matrix notation. Here the query"}, {"duration": 6.479, "start": 975.6, "text": "vectors QI is the result of applying the"}, {"duration": 6.72, "start": 978.72, "text": "down projection matrix WQ down and then"}, {"duration": 5.921, "start": 982.079, "text": "up projection matrix WQ up. The key"}, {"duration": 5.44, "start": 985.44, "text": "vectors KI is the results of applying"}, {"duration": 5.759, "start": 988.0, "text": "the up projection matrix WK up to the"}, {"duration": 5.759, "start": 990.88, "text": "compressed vector CV."}, {"duration": 5.361, "start": 993.759, "text": "This is a cache latent. But what does"}, {"duration": 4.64, "start": 996.639, "text": "this subscript I mean in this up"}, {"duration": 5.2, "start": 999.12, "text": "projection matrices"}, {"duration": 7.201, "start": 1001.279, "text": "the four up projection matrix WQ up and"}, {"duration": 8.8, "start": 1004.32, "text": "W K up maps a vector of dimension DC to"}, {"duration": 6.96, "start": 1008.48, "text": "a vector of dimension DK * H. The eyes"}, {"duration": 4.639, "start": 1013.12, "text": "up projection matrix refers to the"}, {"duration": 5.199, "start": 1015.44, "text": "specific sections of the up projection"}, {"duration": 5.041, "start": 1017.759, "text": "matrix that produce the output for the"}, {"duration": 4.081, "start": 1020.639, "text": "eyes attention head."}, {"duration": 4.08, "start": 1022.8, "text": "Now we can see that the dot product"}, {"duration": 4.319, "start": 1024.72, "text": "between the query and key vectors"}, {"duration": 3.679, "start": 1026.88, "text": "involves the multiplications of three"}, {"duration": 4.0, "start": 1029.039, "text": "matrices."}, {"duration": 4.801, "start": 1030.559, "text": "Due to the associated property, we can"}, {"duration": 5.681, "start": 1033.039, "text": "merge all these matrix multiplications"}, {"duration": 6.0, "start": 1035.36, "text": "into one. This means that we do not need"}, {"duration": 5.839, "start": 1038.72, "text": "to explicitly compute the key vectors"}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 1041.36, "text": "during inference. This is great. But how"}, {"duration": 3.841, "start": 1044.559, "text": "about the operction matrix for the value"}, {"duration": 5.44, "start": 1046.72, "text": "vectors?"}, {"duration": 6.08, "start": 1048.4, "text": "Let's first simplify the equation as ai."}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 1052.16, "text": "This matrix AI stores the attention"}, {"duration": 6.0, "start": 1054.48, "text": "weights for the eyes attention head."}, {"duration": 5.519, "start": 1057.52, "text": "Now recall the value vectors vi is the"}, {"duration": 6.48, "start": 1060.48, "text": "multiplication of the cache laten and"}, {"duration": 6.561, "start": 1063.039, "text": "the up projection matrix w up. This can"}, {"duration": 4.719, "start": 1066.96, "text": "be expressed as a block diagonal matrix"}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 1069.6, "text": "where the up projection matrix for the"}, {"duration": 5.521, "start": 1071.679, "text": "value vectors lies along the diagonal."}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 1074.96, "text": "This suggests that we can absorb the"}, {"duration": 6.88, "start": 1077.2, "text": "upper junction matrix WV up into the"}, {"duration": 6.4, "start": 1080.32, "text": "output matrix WO. By incorporating the"}, {"duration": 4.88, "start": 1084.08, "text": "upperction matrix into the query and"}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 1086.72, "text": "output matrices, we can compute"}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 1088.96, "text": "attention efficiently without incurring"}, {"duration": 4.8, "start": 1092.08, "text": "extra computation."}, {"duration": 5.84, "start": 1094.32, "text": "Excellent. But multi-head latent"}, {"duration": 5.44, "start": 1096.88, "text": "attention has a fundamental limitation."}, {"duration": 6.08, "start": 1100.16, "text": "it is not compatible with rotary"}, {"duration": 5.92, "start": 1102.32, "text": "positional embedding or rope. But why is"}, {"duration": 4.16, "start": 1106.24, "text": "that the case?"}, {"duration": 4.72, "start": 1108.24, "text": "Let's examine how rotary position"}, {"duration": 5.84, "start": 1110.4, "text": "embedding enables the model to capture"}, {"duration": 6.56, "start": 1112.96, "text": "the relative positions of tokens."}, {"duration": 5.76, "start": 1116.24, "text": "Imagine we have a token dog. Assuming"}, {"duration": 5.44, "start": 1119.52, "text": "that all the query and key vectors are"}, {"duration": 5.2, "start": 1122.0, "text": "two-dimensional vectors for now with"}, {"duration": 5.12, "start": 1124.96, "text": "robe the query vector corresponding the"}, {"duration": 5.359, "start": 1127.2, "text": "dog token is transformed by applying a"}, {"duration": 5.599, "start": 1130.08, "text": "rotation that encodes its positional"}, {"duration": 6.161, "start": 1132.559, "text": "information. For example, here we apply"}, {"duration": 6.321, "start": 1135.679, "text": "a rotation of one SA because the dot"}, {"duration": 6.959, "start": 1138.72, "text": "token is at the first position. For the"}, {"duration": 8.0, "start": 1142.0, "text": "sequence my dog we apply rotation of two"}, {"duration": 8.801, "start": 1145.679, "text": "SA. Similarly for the sequence I walk my"}, {"duration": 6.16, "start": 1150.0, "text": "dog, we apply a rotation of four sitta."}, {"duration": 4.4, "start": 1154.48, "text": "Now suppose we want to compute the"}, {"duration": 6.24, "start": 1156.16, "text": "attention to the wall token. We compute"}, {"duration": 6.48, "start": 1158.88, "text": "its key vector. We rotate a vector by"}, {"duration": 7.04, "start": 1162.4, "text": "two sitta because walk is at position"}, {"duration": 7.28, "start": 1165.36, "text": "two. You might be wondering"}, {"duration": 5.599, "start": 1169.44, "text": "rotations like this. It turns out with"}, {"duration": 5.84, "start": 1172.64, "text": "the rotation the attention between the"}, {"duration": 6.241, "start": 1175.039, "text": "query and key vectors of the two tokens"}, {"duration": 5.84, "start": 1178.48, "text": "depend only on their relative position"}, {"duration": 5.68, "start": 1181.28, "text": "in their sequence. For example, we may"}, {"duration": 6.0, "start": 1184.32, "text": "change the sequence to every morning I"}, {"duration": 6.719, "start": 1186.96, "text": "walk my dog. Here the positions of the"}, {"duration": 5.52, "start": 1190.32, "text": "dog and walk token change resulting a"}, {"duration": 5.281, "start": 1193.679, "text": "different rotation transformation being"}, {"duration": 5.199, "start": 1195.84, "text": "applied to their corresponding vectors."}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 1198.96, "text": "But the angle between the two rotated"}, {"duration": 5.441, "start": 1201.039, "text": "vectors remain consistent. This holds"}, {"duration": 5.28, "start": 1204.32, "text": "true regardless how many preceding"}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 1206.48, "text": "tokens there are. This suggests that the"}, {"duration": 4.8, "start": 1209.6, "text": "dot product between the query and the"}, {"duration": 4.719, "start": 1211.84, "text": "key vector now depends on the relative"}, {"duration": 4.96, "start": 1214.4, "text": "token positions."}, {"duration": 5.281, "start": 1216.559, "text": "This is great. But in practice, the"}, {"duration": 4.64, "start": 1219.36, "text": "actual query and key vectors have more"}, {"duration": 4.88, "start": 1221.84, "text": "than two dimensions."}, {"duration": 5.44, "start": 1224.0, "text": "To address this, we divide each vector"}, {"duration": 5.52, "start": 1226.72, "text": "into multiple two-dimensional components"}, {"duration": 5.92, "start": 1229.44, "text": "and apply rotation on each of them with"}, {"duration": 5.6, "start": 1232.24, "text": "different angles, enabling the model to"}, {"duration": 5.679, "start": 1235.36, "text": "encode various frequency of positional"}, {"duration": 5.44, "start": 1237.84, "text": "information throughout the dimensions."}, {"duration": 4.401, "start": 1241.039, "text": "We then concatenate these rotated"}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 1243.28, "text": "two-dimensional components to get the"}, {"duration": 5.68, "start": 1245.44, "text": "final query or key vectors. Let's"}, {"duration": 5.6, "start": 1248.64, "text": "represent this process more concisely"}, {"duration": 5.919, "start": 1251.12, "text": "using matrix vector multiplication."}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 1254.24, "text": "Now we are ready to understand why rope"}, {"duration": 5.041, "start": 1257.039, "text": "is not compatible with multi-head latent"}, {"duration": 4.72, "start": 1259.6, "text": "attention. Here is the dot product"}, {"duration": 5.839, "start": 1262.08, "text": "between a query vector and all the key"}, {"duration": 7.2, "start": 1264.32, "text": "vectors. CKV is the compressed cache"}, {"duration": 6.64, "start": 1267.919, "text": "latent. The upjection matrix for the key"}, {"duration": 6.56, "start": 1271.52, "text": "and query vectors can be absorbed into a"}, {"duration": 5.921, "start": 1274.559, "text": "single matrix. However, with rope as"}, {"duration": 5.04, "start": 1278.08, "text": "illustrated on the left, we encode the"}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 1280.48, "text": "absolute positions of query and key"}, {"duration": 5.039, "start": 1283.12, "text": "vectors through rotations."}, {"duration": 5.04, "start": 1285.84, "text": "This is problematic since the rotation"}, {"duration": 6.081, "start": 1288.159, "text": "matrix lie between the upperction matrix"}, {"duration": 6.48, "start": 1290.88, "text": "for the query and key. We can no longer"}, {"duration": 6.08, "start": 1294.24, "text": "absorb the upper ejection matrix WK up"}, {"duration": 5.28, "start": 1297.36, "text": "during inference. As a result, during"}, {"duration": 5.28, "start": 1300.32, "text": "inference, we must recomputee the keys"}, {"duration": 5.76, "start": 1302.64, "text": "for all preceding tokens, which decrease"}, {"duration": 4.48, "start": 1305.6, "text": "inference efficiency. To address this"}, {"duration": 3.92, "start": 1308.4, "text": "challenge, we need to introduce"}, {"duration": 5.44, "start": 1310.08, "text": "additional multi head queries and a"}, {"duration": 6.64, "start": 1312.32, "text": "share key in order to effectively encode"}, {"duration": 5.76, "start": 1315.52, "text": "position information when using rope. We"}, {"duration": 5.199, "start": 1318.96, "text": "concatenate the original query key"}, {"duration": 4.72, "start": 1321.28, "text": "vectors and the rotated ones as the"}, {"duration": 5.041, "start": 1324.159, "text": "input to the multihat attention"}, {"duration": 5.44, "start": 1326.0, "text": "computation. This approach is known as"}, {"duration": 4.16, "start": 1329.2, "text": "decoupled rope."}, {"duration": 5.599, "start": 1331.44, "text": "These multih high latent attentions"}, {"duration": 7.439, "start": 1333.36, "text": "powers recent a such as deepc R1 and"}, {"duration": 6.481, "start": 1337.039, "text": "Kimmy K2. However, as we generate more"}, {"duration": 4.801, "start": 1340.799, "text": "tokens, we must calculate a tension"}, {"duration": 4.159, "start": 1343.52, "text": "between the current token and all"}, {"duration": 4.319, "start": 1345.6, "text": "preceding tokens."}, {"duration": 4.321, "start": 1347.679, "text": "This results in a slower token per"}, {"duration": 4.24, "start": 1349.919, "text": "second throughput."}, {"duration": 5.679, "start": 1352.0, "text": "To fix this, Deep Seek proposed a"}, {"duration": 5.841, "start": 1354.159, "text": "lightning indexer. The key concept is to"}, {"duration": 5.12, "start": 1357.679, "text": "quickly assess the relevance of each"}, {"duration": 5.76, "start": 1360.0, "text": "token and select only the most relevant"}, {"duration": 5.521, "start": 1362.799, "text": "ones for attention computation."}, {"duration": 5.76, "start": 1365.76, "text": "This is the key idea behind DeepSync"}, {"duration": 5.28, "start": 1368.32, "text": "sparse attention DSA."}, {"duration": 4.96, "start": 1371.52, "text": "But how do we implement this lightning"}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 1373.6, "text": "indexer? The lightning indexer"}, {"duration": 4.72, "start": 1376.48, "text": "calculates an index score between the"}, {"duration": 5.199, "start": 1378.96, "text": "current query token and a previous"}, {"duration": 5.68, "start": 1381.2, "text": "token. These scores helps the model"}, {"duration": 5.601, "start": 1384.159, "text": "decide which previous tokens the query"}, {"duration": 4.48, "start": 1386.88, "text": "should attend to. We use a computation"}, {"duration": 3.279, "start": 1389.76, "text": "that is similar to the multi-head"}, {"duration": 3.679, "start": 1391.36, "text": "attention."}, {"duration": 4.64, "start": 1393.039, "text": "Specifically, we compute individual"}, {"duration": 5.281, "start": 1395.039, "text": "query vectors for each head while using"}, {"duration": 5.761, "start": 1397.679, "text": "a single key vector that is shared among"}, {"duration": 5.599, "start": 1400.32, "text": "all heads. We then compute a dot product"}, {"duration": 5.68, "start": 1403.44, "text": "between a query at position t and the"}, {"duration": 5.921, "start": 1405.919, "text": "key vectors at position s. We discard"}, {"duration": 4.48, "start": 1409.12, "text": "the negative values with ru and multiply"}, {"duration": 4.959, "start": 1411.84, "text": "it with the weights derived from the"}, {"duration": 6.48, "start": 1413.6, "text": "query token at position t. Adding this"}, {"duration": 5.521, "start": 1416.799, "text": "up give us the index score. As with"}, {"duration": 5.44, "start": 1420.08, "text": "multih highlight attention, we apply"}, {"duration": 5.68, "start": 1422.32, "text": "rope to only a subset of dimensions and"}, {"duration": 5.76, "start": 1425.52, "text": "then concatenate the rotated and the"}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 1428.0, "text": "original unrotated vector components."}, {"duration": 3.92, "start": 1431.28, "text": "Same for all the key vectors from the"}, {"duration": 4.799, "start": 1433.36, "text": "previous tokens."}, {"duration": 5.52, "start": 1435.2, "text": "This is called partial rope. Now you may"}, {"duration": 4.801, "start": 1438.159, "text": "wonder as this indexer also compute the"}, {"duration": 4.64, "start": 1440.72, "text": "attention between the query vector and"}, {"duration": 4.079, "start": 1442.96, "text": "all the key vectors. Why would this be"}, {"duration": 4.0, "start": 1445.36, "text": "efficient?"}, {"duration": 4.64, "start": 1447.039, "text": "The key step is to quantize the query"}, {"duration": 4.0, "start": 1449.36, "text": "and key vectors into 8 bits"}, {"duration": 4.24, "start": 1451.679, "text": "representations."}, {"duration": 4.96, "start": 1453.36, "text": "Using a lower position is fine because"}, {"duration": 4.88, "start": 1455.919, "text": "our main goal is to identify the most"}, {"duration": 4.64, "start": 1458.32, "text": "relevant tokens rather than compute the"}, {"duration": 4.0, "start": 1460.799, "text": "exact attention scores."}, {"duration": 4.16, "start": 1462.96, "text": "Quantization offers a coarse"}, {"duration": 5.841, "start": 1464.799, "text": "approximation greatly speeding up the"}, {"duration": 5.84, "start": 1467.12, "text": "calculation of index scores. However,"}, {"duration": 5.519, "start": 1470.64, "text": "naively quantize the query and key"}, {"duration": 5.76, "start": 1472.96, "text": "vectors may result in inaccuracy."}, {"duration": 4.561, "start": 1476.159, "text": "To mitigate this issue, we need to apply"}, {"duration": 4.16, "start": 1478.72, "text": "a rotation."}, {"duration": 4.079, "start": 1480.72, "text": "What does it mean?"}, {"duration": 4.48, "start": 1482.88, "text": "Let's take a look at the dot product"}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 1484.799, "text": "between a queried vector QT [music] and"}, {"duration": 6.16, "start": 1487.36, "text": "a key vector KS."}, {"duration": 6.64, "start": 1490.159, "text": "Sometimes some entries have large values"}, {"duration": 5.2, "start": 1493.52, "text": "while some have very small values."}, {"duration": 5.201, "start": 1496.799, "text": "Floating point formats with higher"}, {"duration": 5.52, "start": 1498.72, "text": "positions such as floating 16 or above"}, {"duration": 5.279, "start": 1502.0, "text": "can accurately represent the full"}, {"duration": 5.2, "start": 1504.24, "text": "dynamic range of these values."}, {"duration": 4.321, "start": 1507.279, "text": "But it becomes problematic when we"}, {"duration": 3.68, "start": 1509.44, "text": "quantize these vectors with lower"}, {"duration": 4.079, "start": 1511.6, "text": "precision."}, {"duration": 5.76, "start": 1513.12, "text": "Let's work with a specific example of"}, {"duration": 6.801, "start": 1515.679, "text": "four-dimensional vector. Here each"}, {"duration": 5.919, "start": 1518.88, "text": "vector has both large and small values."}, {"duration": 5.92, "start": 1522.48, "text": "One simple idea is to multiply the"}, {"duration": 5.521, "start": 1524.799, "text": "vectors with a random orthogonal matrix."}, {"duration": 4.8, "start": 1528.4, "text": "The goal of this matrix [music] is to"}, {"duration": 6.32, "start": 1530.32, "text": "mix up the values of multiple entries in"}, {"duration": 5.839, "start": 1533.2, "text": "a vector. More specifically, the entry"}, {"duration": 5.279, "start": 1536.64, "text": "of the output vector is a weighted"}, {"duration": 5.681, "start": 1539.039, "text": "combination of all entries in the input"}, {"duration": 5.201, "start": 1541.919, "text": "vector. This makes the values in the"}, {"duration": 5.36, "start": 1544.72, "text": "output vectors well spread without"}, {"duration": 5.76, "start": 1547.12, "text": "extreme values. But this requires"}, {"duration": 4.8, "start": 1550.08, "text": "another matrix multiplication."}, {"duration": 5.6, "start": 1552.88, "text": "A simpler and even more effective"}, {"duration": 5.919, "start": 1554.88, "text": "approach is to use transform. After"}, {"duration": 4.96, "start": 1558.48, "text": "applying the hard transform, the output"}, {"duration": 5.601, "start": 1560.799, "text": "vectors are deterministically computed"}, {"duration": 5.839, "start": 1563.44, "text": "and exhibit a uniform mixing across all"}, {"duration": 5.6, "start": 1566.4, "text": "coordinates. The hard transform"}, {"duration": 5.361, "start": 1569.279, "text": "effectively spreads out large spikes"}, {"duration": 6.0, "start": 1572.0, "text": "across all coordinates allowing the"}, {"duration": 5.44, "start": 1574.64, "text": "quantizer to retain more information."}, {"duration": 4.96, "start": 1578.0, "text": "This transform can be implemented"}, {"duration": 6.16, "start": 1580.08, "text": "effectively with highly optimized GPU"}, {"duration": 5.199, "start": 1582.96, "text": "kernels. Furthermore, in practice, we"}, {"duration": 5.6, "start": 1586.24, "text": "don't need to compute the multiplication"}, {"duration": 6.561, "start": 1588.159, "text": "with this dense hot matrix. Instead, we"}, {"duration": 5.28, "start": 1591.84, "text": "use a fast wash transform which"}, {"duration": 5.04, "start": 1594.72, "text": "efficiently computes multiplication by a"}, {"duration": 5.28, "start": 1597.12, "text": "hot matrix without explicitly"}, {"duration": 6.48, "start": 1599.76, "text": "constructing the matrix relying solely"}, {"duration": 6.8, "start": 1602.4, "text": "on addition and subtraction operations."}, {"duration": 5.6, "start": 1606.24, "text": "Let's get a sense of how this works. We"}, {"duration": 5.359, "start": 1609.2, "text": "randomly generate query and key vectors"}, {"duration": 4.24, "start": 1611.84, "text": "and compute the mean errors over 5,000"}, {"duration": 3.6, "start": 1614.559, "text": "samples."}, {"duration": 4.64, "start": 1616.08, "text": "This is the baseline results when we"}, {"duration": 5.841, "start": 1618.159, "text": "directly quantize the vectors into eight"}, {"duration": 7.199, "start": 1620.72, "text": "bits. When applying a random orthogonal"}, {"duration": 6.159, "start": 1624.0, "text": "matrix, we reduce the arrow slightly."}, {"duration": 5.041, "start": 1627.919, "text": "Applying the hardon transform give us"}, {"duration": 5.441, "start": 1630.159, "text": "the most accurate approximation."}, {"duration": 5.599, "start": 1632.96, "text": "An additional advantage is its improved"}, {"duration": 5.52, "start": 1635.6, "text": "stability as indicated by a lower"}, {"duration": 4.72, "start": 1638.559, "text": "standard deviation by using the"}, {"duration": 4.799, "start": 1641.12, "text": "lightning indexer to efficiently"}, {"duration": 5.361, "start": 1643.279, "text": "identify the most relevant tokens. Deep"}, {"duration": 4.88, "start": 1645.919, "text": "seek sparse attention enables two to"}, {"duration": 4.399, "start": 1648.64, "text": "three times faster processing of long"}, {"duration": 6.321, "start": 1650.799, "text": "sequences while reducing memory"}, {"duration": 6.081, "start": 1653.039, "text": "consumption by around 30 to 40%. The"}, {"duration": 4.159, "start": 1657.12, "text": "exciting part is that this efficiency"}, {"duration": 5.6, "start": 1659.12, "text": "boosts maintain the same level of"}, {"duration": 5.121, "start": 1661.279, "text": "performance as previous model. Now let's"}, {"duration": 4.88, "start": 1664.72, "text": "see how we can train this lightning"}, {"duration": 5.04, "start": 1666.4, "text": "indexer. In the [music] first stage, we"}, {"duration": 4.16, "start": 1669.6, "text": "freeze the main multiand latent"}, {"duration": 5.52, "start": 1671.44, "text": "attention layer and only update the"}, {"duration": 5.2, "start": 1673.76, "text": "parameters of the lightning indexer. To"}, {"duration": 3.599, "start": 1676.96, "text": "construct the target distribution, we"}, {"duration": 4.319, "start": 1678.96, "text": "begin by summing the main attention"}, {"duration": 5.12, "start": 1680.559, "text": "scores across all hands for each query"}, {"duration": 4.4, "start": 1683.279, "text": "token, followed by applying A1"}, {"duration": 3.681, "start": 1685.679, "text": "normalization along the sequence"}, {"duration": 4.161, "start": 1687.679, "text": "dimension."}, {"duration": 5.12, "start": 1689.36, "text": "This dense warm up stage aligns the"}, {"duration": 4.16, "start": 1691.84, "text": "indexer's output with the main attention"}, {"duration": 3.84, "start": 1694.48, "text": "distribution."}, {"duration": 4.72, "start": 1696.0, "text": "After warming up the indexer, we add"}, {"duration": 4.719, "start": 1698.32, "text": "fine grain token selection and trend all"}, {"duration": 4.559, "start": 1700.72, "text": "the model parameters so that the model"}, {"duration": 4.161, "start": 1703.039, "text": "can learn the sparse attention patterns"}, {"duration": 3.841, "start": 1705.279, "text": "of DSA."}, {"duration": 4.32, "start": 1707.2, "text": "During this stage, we still encourage"}, {"duration": 4.72, "start": 1709.12, "text": "the indexer to match the main attention"}, {"duration": 4.0, "start": 1711.52, "text": "distribution but only for the selected"}, {"duration": 4.0, "start": 1713.84, "text": "tokens."}, {"duration": 4.879, "start": 1715.52, "text": "We also detach the indexer input from"}, {"duration": 6.0, "start": 1717.84, "text": "the computational graph allowing us to"}, {"duration": 6.0, "start": 1720.399, "text": "optimize it separately. The indexer is"}, {"duration": 5.04, "start": 1723.84, "text": "trained only on its own loss while the"}, {"duration": 5.121, "start": 1726.399, "text": "main model is optimized solely on the"}, {"duration": 4.72, "start": 1728.88, "text": "language modeling loss."}, {"duration": 4.48, "start": 1731.52, "text": "I hope these videos provides the basic"}, {"duration": 4.319, "start": 1733.6, "text": "idea of the attention mechanism and"}, {"duration": 4.559, "start": 1736.0, "text": "various techniques to improve its"}, {"duration": 5.201, "start": 1737.919, "text": "efficiency. Thanks for watching and I'll"}, {"duration": 2.561, "start": 1740.559, "text": "see you next"}], "video_id": "Y-o545eYjXM"}